caption: Fantastic food. Amazing service. Absolutely stunning interior. Do yourself a favor and give this place a try if you haven’t yet!

Best comfort food in the city! Support this local business! Give them a try.  We were there recently to shoot a beverage commercial (not for the restaurant). Everyone there was extremely friendly and professional. They are very covid compliant, as well. Definitely try their SHRIMP & GRITS.

I had the family meal with pork chop, mashed potato, kale salad, roasted veggies, and chocolate caramel cake. The quality of the food was absolutely amazing and the value was also very good.The pork chop was crispy and perfectly cooked and mashed potato was buttery and creamy. The kale salad was fresh too. I loved the dressing.

Thanks to the pandemic, take-out was the only available option... really miss eating in this comfortable space and interacting with the wonderful team of folks at Taste 222.  Ordered the Taste 222 Burger and Sourdough Grilled Cheese online for pick-up for lunch today.  Both sandwiches were ordered with side salads.  All of the food was fresh and delicious!  Ketchup and salad dressings were packaged in their own separate containers to keep food from getting soggy.  Paid online and pickup was a breeze... friendly staff member, clean and inviting table where packaged orders were presented safely, and items placed in appropriately sized containers.  ONLY issue I have is that you cannot add tip when you order and pay online, so left a cash tip when I picked up the order.  Will definitely be back for carry-out until indoor dining is allowed again.  Thanks Taste 222!
Elegant.  Can't wait for it to open
Very crowded, don't expect your table at the time you have your reservation. I would highly recommend if you are in Taste 222
The food & wines served were all amazing.   Thanks for a great night & the inspiration to try some new dishes when we get back home.
This place has the best food and service!
Yum. Yum. And YUM! Super quick delivery and the food was   fresh and hot. Ordered the bourbon ribs, Mac n cheese, and roasted vegetables. Would definitely return!
We ordered a family chicken dinner and it was delicious. It was a ton of food and very reasonably priced. This is a new favorite added to our list.
We love Taste 222 especially their family meals during this shelter in place.  Best comfort food in the city!!!

I ordered from the Taste to Go Menu and it was absolutely delicious! The meal description says it provides a serving for four people, but i was doubtful. I thought for sure the meal would feed two people with a little left over. I am happy to say I was very wrong. Our meal comfortably fed four adults with enough sides to have seconds. I am very pleased with my quarantine meal and am looking forward to seeing what they have to offer for Mother's Day! Thank you Taste 222

Great place to have a a quick and relaxing lunch, awesome staff! very accommodating (Had some in with a party of ten which ended up 14, they bent backwards to accommodate us! Highly recommend this hidden spot!

Had. Girls Night Out event at Taste 222, and we loved it   The food was delicious, the wait staff was attentive and we had a great table for 10.  Would definitely recommend!

The wait staff has to be the nicest staff out there. They have some amazing grits and shrimp (grits are cheesy) and the apple cider is amazing! The chicken and waffles were good as (Both chicken and waffles were cooked to a nice crisp) but the donuts holes is were it’s at. They come out hot cover in a Cinnamon sugar and powder sugar served with a caramel dipping sauce. If I knew this before I order my entree; I would have ordered a coffee and those donut holes and been good.

Thank you so much Iman and the rest of the Taste 222 family. The customer service experience that I received was beyond expectations and I appreciate the handling of my order mishap. This quality of service is very rare in this city so I thank you all again! Oh and the food is AMAZING!!
Exquisite ambiance, cuisine, and service every time.
Great food, great service.

Never going back. Best thing was seating area in the very front left of entrance as it was quiet, you could hear well and carry on a conversation easily without yelling. Food and drink was another thing. My friend and I both ordered the burger during happy hour and they weren’t good at all. They tasted plant based and not like real beef. Assembly of burger was sloppy as well and we didn’t eat but a few bites and left the rest. Drinks were just ok too. They need to carry top shelf liquors. One thing that was really bad was after we were done eating and the waiter brought the bill, then immediately he kept coming back to cash out. He even came and looked in the folder to take and cash out. This is very perturbing when you are trying to relax after a hard day. We did tell him we might get another drink but after trying to rush us out, we just paid and left. We are only talking about a bill that was for a total of 2 drinks folks between the 2 of us!!! It was not busy no one was waiting and it was only 8pm on a week night no less, so why rush us? Worst experience! I almost felt like throwing the bill and my credit card at him so he would leave us alone! Need to re-train the wait staff to be courteous and learn timing. People will pay their bill when they are ready so don’t rush us!!! We aren’t leaving town on a 2 drink bill and bar food! Really!!!
Five star food and five star service! Add Taste 222 to your top ten list.

Planned on going their for happy hour on 10/17/19 but the staff couldn't accommodate a party of four. The explaination was that happy hour was under way and and their was an event going on. Clearly their was tables not being occupied but  still wouldn't couldn't seat us. Bummer I loved this place  but, after this I will not be patronizing this establishment again.
It was ok, little overpriced. I'm sure we'll go back because it's so close but a lot of better options in the area.

Had a nice lunch for my husband's birthday. Service was prompt, food was delicious and portions were a good size. My tri tip steak salad was lovely, I would probably not get it with the cranberries again, too many. I would have appreciated bread Service. And I hate tepid water. Serve water ice cold! It's a spot to grab a drink and a working lunch on your companies tab.

Just had a business lunch today.  Very impressed the the service from the hostess to our server.  Friendly and helpful.  I had the fresh salmon poke and  it was fantastic.  Looking forward to coming back soon.

This review reflects my experience with the manager on staff in the evening of 5/16/19. I ordered medium rare lamb chops and they came back close to well done. I don't really like to send food back and didn't have the time to wait on a second preparation. Instead, I informed my waiter that the meat temperature was not what I ordered.  He informed the manager and had him come over. I spoke with him and he noted my comment and said it would be taken care of. When the bill arrived, he took $3 off of a $115 bill. He noted he gave us a 15% discount on the lamb.  In general, I felt that response to be quite insulting. I don't have a large following on this social media, but I will give all of my friends and colleagues my honest review of this place. Food is 3/5. Wait staff is attentive and good. Management I experienced left a lot more to be desired.

Went here for dinner in the summertime.  Taste 222 is an elegantly intimate place to stop in for a drink, appetizer or meal with friends or business associates.  It's also a nice place to stop in after work and have a drink with colleagues or an intimate dinner with your loved one.  Taste 222 consists of a Large room with a high ceiling, there are 4 tables with seating for four people. There are 8 single seats in front of the kitchen, as well as seating at the long bar.  For people looking  for just a drink or an appetizer there is also couch seating in the corner.  We started off with a charcuterie which is smoked salmon, prosciutto, finocchiona, and a chef's selection of cheeses . It was a great start to a wonderful dinner. We tried the seared lamb chops, which were very tasteful, and I wanted more.   The Creole shrimp is more of a meal with seared Cajun shrimp, jalapeno goat cheese cornbread and a delicious Opelousas sauce.  By far the best dish I had was the dessert, the three layers chocolate caramel cake from Brown Sugar Bakery was huge, delicious,  and enough for 4 people to share.  Although the decor is upscale the waitress was very casually dressed, which I did not understand, maybe because it was a weeknight  With a menu that characterizes their dinners as small plates, just be aware that they are just that, small plates. Portions are small but be adventurous and order several to share.
